Interface IEventManager


  • public interface IEventManager

        <TEventData> long notify(TEventData event)
        Calls all existing listeners of the given type of event

        Returns:

      • notify

        <TEventData> long notify(Class<TEventData> eventClass)
        Calls all existing listeners of the given type of event. The listeners get null as eventData in order not to create empty instances of events
        Type Parameters:
        TEventData - the type of the desired event
        Parameters:
        eventClass - the type of the desired event. All listeners get null as parameter
        Returns:
        the number of the called listeners

      • notifyAnyway

        <TEventData> long notifyAnyway(TEventData event)
        Calls all listeners of the given type of event. If there are no listeners, the event is deferred and is invoked on the subscription to the event
        Type Parameters:
        TEventData - the type of the desired event
        Parameters:
        event - an instance of the desired event. All listeners get this instance as parameter
        Returns:
        the number of the called listeners

      • notifyAnyway

        <TEventData> long notifyAnyway(Class<TEventData> eventClass)
        Calls all listeners of the given type of event. If there are no listeners, the event is deferred and is invoked on the subscription to the event

        The listeners get null as eventData in order not to create empty instances of events

        Type Parameters:
        TEventData - the type of the desired event
        Parameters:
        eventClass - the desired type of event. All listeners get null as parameter
        Returns:
        the number of the called listeners
